string.description: Quick-Books client. By default uses DefaultQuickBooksOnlineClient class.
string.caption: Client Reference

string.description: The base uri used by the QBO SDK for QuickBooks Online requests. Used to make all QuickBooks Online requests.
string.caption: Base Uri

string.description: The base uri used by the QBO SDK for Platform Services requests. Used to make all Intuit Platform requests.
string.caption: Platform Base Uri
string.name: platformBaseUri

integer.description: The connection timeout in ms for Quickbooks Data Services used by the QBO SDK.
integer.caption: Connection Time Out

integer.description: The request timeout in ms for Quickbooks Data Services used by the QBO SDK.
integer.caption: Request Time Out
integer.name: requestTimeOut

integer.description: The number of retries for a failed request used by the QBO SDK.

integer.caption: Retry Interval
integer.name: retryInterval

string.description: Prefix used for storing credentials in ObjectStore. It will be concatenated to the access token identifier. E.g. prefix: "qb_", user identifier (realmId): "12345", key for object store "qb_12345".
string.caption: Access Token Identifier Prefix
string.name: accessTokenIdentifierPrefix

boolean.description: Specifies if the OpenID response will be verified. By default it is true.
boolean.caption: Verify Open Id Response
boolean.name: verifyOpenIdResponse

globalRef.description: Specify which configuration to use for this invocation.
globalRef.caption: Config Reference
globalRef.name: config-ref

cloud-connector.description: QuickBooks software provides an interface that allows you to use forms such as checks, deposit slips and invoices, making the accounting process more comfortable for the average business owner or manager. By using the built-in functions that pertain to your business, you are able to perform your company accounting by simply recording your vendor activities, customer activities, banking transactions, payroll checks and taxes. QuickBooks handles the accounting portion of each transaction behind the scenes. Read more: QuickBooks Accounting Tutorial | eHow.com http://www.ehow.com/way_5462311_quickbooks-accounting-tutorial.html#ixzz1csaydwxl.
cloud-connector.caption: Quickbooks Online

string.description: Optional value for identifying the requestToken. If it is not passed the client will use a UUID.

string.description: Instance of a IEntity to be deleted by Data Services.
string.caption: Object Reference

string.description: Id which is assigned by Data Services when the object is created.
string.caption: Id
string.name: id

string.description: Integer that indicates how many times the object has been updated. Before performing the update, Data Services verifies that the SyncToken in the request has the same value as the SyncToken in the Data Service's repository.
string.caption: Sync Token
string.name: syncToken

string.description: Credentials identifier for the user information to be requested.
string.caption: Access Token Id

string.description: Id used for identifying the authorized request token. It comes within the callback. By default the query string parameter is userId.
string.caption: Request Token Id

string.description: Id used for store the accessToken in the Object Store. By default the value is the realmId.
string.caption: User Identifier
string.name: userIdentifier

string.description: OAuth verifier. It comes within the callback. The default value is "#[header:inbound:oauth_verifier]".
string.caption: Verifier

string.description: Credentials identifier for the user information to be requested.
string.caption: Access Token Id

string.description: Regex for extracting the information The regex has to extract the information in this way: match[0]: "appId,appName,contextArea" match[1]: "logoImageUrl" The method will split the application information to generate the @link{AppMenuInformation object.
string.caption: Regex
string.name: regex

string.description: OpenID callbackUrl. It has to point to an endpoint callback to process the response.
